  "text": "Since we perform pruning at the attribute level of the QAR mining problem, the set of frequent itemsets produced by MIC is a subset of that produced by SAM. Consequently, the set of QARs generated by MIC is also a subset of that generated by SAM. However, we emphasize that our method is not an approximation technique that improves the efficiency at the expense of accuracy. Instead, we show that MIC not only significantly outperforms SAM, but the rules we obtain are also of higher quality than that obtained by SAM, as measured using interest [CITATION_1] , which is a well-established measure for the interestingness of an association rule.",
